<h1>FAQ</h1>
<div class="container">
  <div class="panel-group" id="accordion">
    <div class="faqHeader">General</div>
    <div class="panel panel-default">
      <div class="panel-heading">
        <h4 class="panel-title">
          <a class="accordion-toggle" data-toggle="collapse" data-parent="#accordion" href="#collapse1">Do I need an account?</a>
        </h4>
      </div>
      <div id="collapse1" class="panel-collapse collapse">
        <div class="panel-body">
          No. You can access your wallet using an account, or only with your seed.
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="panel panel-default">
      <div class="panel-heading">
        <h4 class="panel-title">
          <a class="accordion-toggle" data-toggle="collapse" data-parent="#accordion" href="#collapse2">I lost my password. What do I do?</a>
        </h4>
      </div>
      <div id="collapse2" class="panel-collapse collapse">
        <div class="panel-body">
          We don't store your password, and will not be able to retrieve it. If you still have your seed, you can use it
          to access your account.
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="panel panel-default">
      <div class="panel-heading">
        <h4 class="panel-title">
          <a class="accordion-toggle" data-toggle="collapse" data-parent="#accordion" href="#collapse13">Transactions and address generation takes forever. Why?</a>
        </h4>
      </div>
      <div id="collapse13" class="panel-collapse collapse">
        <div class="panel-body">
          <p>When making a transaction, your browser have to do proof of work. This is similar to what bitcoin miners have
            to do, but with IOTA this is done by the senders. If your computer is slow, this could take some time.</p>
          <p>Another thing to be aware of is that some browsers reduce the processing power of tabs when you leave them.
            You should therefore make sure to stay on the site until the work is done (sadly, we do not control this). </p>
          <p>Another approach for chrome users would be to do the transaction in a new window instead of a new tab. As
            long as the tab is selected in the new window, you are free to browse in the original chrome window without
            reducing processing power.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="panel panel-default">
      <div class="panel-heading">
        <h4 class="panel-title">
          <a class="accordion-toggle" data-toggle="collapse" data-parent="#accordion" href="#collapse14">My balance is gone/too low</a>
        </h4>
      </div>
      <div id="collapse14" class="panel-collapse collapse">
        <div class="panel-body">
          <p>There can be 2 reasons for this.</p>
          <p>Your IOTAs are stored on addresses, which again belong to your seed. When you enter the wallet, it will
            load up to 30 of your last addresses. If you have more than 30 addresses, and some of the first ones have a
            positive balance, the seed balance will be wrong. </p><p><b>Solution: </b>This can easily be fixed by pressing the "Load all"
            button in your wallet. Consider to move all your funds to one address when this happens.</p>
          <p>Another reason why the balance may not show up is if there has recently been a snapshot on the IOTA network.
          When a snapshot is taken, all unnecessary data is basically removed from the network. The result is that
            the wallet sometimes won't be able to find all your addresses. </p>
          </p><p><b>Solution: </b>Press the "Generate new address" button until your balance is correct.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="faqHeader">Security</div>
    <div class="panel panel-default">
      <div class="panel-heading">
        <h4 class="panel-title">
          <a class="accordion-toggle collapsed" data-toggle="collapse" data-parent="#accordion" href="#collapse3">Is this secure?</a>
        </h4>
      </div>
      <div id="collapse3" class="panel-collapse collapse">
        <div class="panel-body">
          No sensitive information ever leaves your client. If you register an account your seed immediately gets
          encrypted before it is transferred to our server. That means we will never be able to restore your seed if you
          loose it or your log in credentials.
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="panel panel-default">
      <div class="panel-heading">
        <h4 class="panel-title">
          <a class="accordion-toggle collapsed" data-toggle="collapse" data-parent="#accordion" href="#collapse4">What happens if I loose my seed?</a>
        </h4>
      </div>
      <div id="collapse4" class="panel-collapse collapse">
        <div class="panel-body">
          <p>If you loose your seed and do not have a account, your iotas are gone.</p>
          <p>It is always advised that you keep a backup of your seed somewhere safe</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="panel panel-default">
      <div class="panel-heading">
        <h4 class="panel-title">
          <a class="accordion-toggle collapsed" data-toggle="collapse" data-parent="#accordion" href="#collapse5">Is my seed safe with you?</a>
        </h4>
      </div>
      <div id="collapse5" class="panel-collapse collapse">
        <div class="panel-body">
          We never get access to your seed. Every action that require a seed is made locally on your device.
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="panel panel-default">
      <div class="panel-heading">
        <h4 class="panel-title">
          <a class="accordion-toggle collapsed" data-toggle="collapse" data-parent="#accordion" href="#collapse6">What happens if the site goes down?</a>
        </h4>
      </div>
      <div id="collapse6" class="panel-collapse collapse">
        <div class="panel-body">
          Then you will still be able to access your IOTA account if you have your seed. You can for example use the desktop wallet.
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="panel panel-default">
      <div class="panel-heading">
        <h4 class="panel-title">
          <a class="accordion-toggle collapsed" data-toggle="collapse" data-parent="#accordion" href="#collapse8">How can I be sure you're not scamming?</a>
        </h4>
      </div>
      <div id="collapse8" class="panel-collapse collapse">
