    <div class="panel panel-default">
      <div class="panel-heading">
        <h4 class="panel-title">
          <a class="accordion-toggle" data-toggle="collapse" data-parent="#accordion" href="#collapse11">What does it mean to replay/re-attach?</a>
        </h4>
      </div>
      <div id="collapse11" class="panel-collapse collapse">
        <div class="panel-body">
          <p>When you replay a transaction, it is basically moved to a different part of the tangle, which may be more active.
            The reason for doing this is to increase the chances of it being picked up and validated by others</p>
          <p>iota-wallet.org replays/re-attaches your transactions automatically, so you don't normally have to think
            about it. If you on the other hand have a transaction that have been pending for a long time, you may want
            to replay it yourself.</p>
          <p> Also note the we don't allow you to replay double spends, because they can never be confirmed.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="panel panel-default">
    <div class="panel-heading">
      <h4 class="panel-title">
        <a class="accordion-toggle" data-toggle="collapse" data-parent="#accordion" href="#collapse14">What is a double spend?</a>
      </h4>
    </div>
    <div id="collapse14" class="panel-collapse collapse">
      <div class="panel-body">
        <p>IOTA addresses become insecure to use after it have been used to make a transaction. Because of this, this is what happens when you make a transaction:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>A list of your addresses with a positive balance is collected, and is used to fund the transaction</li>
          <li>The transaction is made by doing proof of work. You validate two other transactions at the same time</li>
          <li>All remaining funds on the addresses used in step 1 is transferred to a newly generated address</li>
        </ul>
        <p>What this means is that if you send two transactions from the same address, one of them will be confirmed,
          and the addresses will have a balance of 0. The remaining transaction will therefore never be confirmed, because
          it don't have enough funds</p>
        <p>If this happens, the solution is simple: Do the pending transaction again. iota-wallet.org provides a warning
          before every attempt to double spend. If you get such a warning, simply wait until the last outgoing transaction
          has been confirmed</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
    <div class="panel panel-default">
      <div class="panel-heading">
        <h4 class="panel-title">
          <a class="accordion-toggle" data-toggle="collapse" data-parent="#accordion" href="#collapse12">Should I re-attach or make the transaction again?</a>
        </h4>
      </div>
      <div id="collapse12" class="panel-collapse collapse">
        <div class="panel-body">
          By opening the transaction, one of the following will be true:
          <ul>
            <li>You see a green re-attach button. </li>
            <li>You get a red warning telling you that the transaction is a double spend. In that case you will have to do the transaction again manually</li>
          </ul>
          iota-wallet.org replays your transactions automatically, but if it have been pending a long time and it is not
          a double spend, you can choose to replay it yourself.
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
